rComments: Fantastic course, loved it! Rukhsana is passionate encouraging of her students. Her knowledge is eventually valuable for her students.
Was not sure at first, but do like the online part. Well organization!!
Loved doing a real project:-)
I liked how she was accommodating and even let us have an extra quiz to help boost our marks!

She is pretty uptight with her work and follows every single rule and regulation to the T, she makes you sign a contract at the beginning of the course, and if you dont sign she won't mark your work... However she is caring and gives good feedback.
I would take her class again!

Felt disrespected as a student, she came off as rude and careless. Her lectures are light in content but her explanations and examples are very confusing, need to look it up after to clarify. Textb makes things way more clear,interesting and useful. Sadly,her lectures didn't do the same, maybe its cuz my usual experience in uni is the opposite.

Disrespect students at all. She loves to show off her knowledge, but she where does she get all that confidence? She is tough and totally not an understandable prof, I think to be a prof will need to be a lot better than she does. Try to avoid her class, totally disaster.

Dr Rukhsana is one of the best profs at the department of communication if not the best. She is really a dedicated prof who is always ready to help, inside and outside the class.  With regard to this course, I believe that no one can teach this course as good as Dr Rukhsana dose. She is knowledgeable. I highly recommend taking this class with her.

Dry teaching style. Every slide is the exact same, no stimulation. Brings in guest speakers who are her own students at the graduate level who knew less about their projects than we did. She constantly stops and asks the class to answer a question, and never catches on that the class isn't going to answer and is half asleep. Btw she went to Ohio.
group dynamics should be taught by someone who in fact has some social skills or team skills :/
I liked her teaching style - she made it an easy-going and open environment where it was easy to speak and feel a part of the class discussion. The course was well-designed and helpful.

Why go to the class and pay for this class if the teacher just reads off her slides. Doesn't look like she likes teaching, if you ask questions she gets frustrated, annoying, boring and just total waste of time

If you want to see someone praising themselves and show off then go ahead and take the class. She tries to show she is tough but hey you need some credentials yourself to have such confidence, right? Total disappointment.
Simply terrible. I thought people need to have some credentials to become a prof. Guess what I was wrong :(
There were a lot of assignments. But the exams were pretty fair.
As I recall the teaching is stimulating and very interesting. We had many ways to learn and present what we learned in class. Do take this class with her.
I liked the professor's teaching method. She was very approcahble and she made students feel equal + at the same level. I recommend this class!
I enjoyed this class because she had an original approach to the course. She created a comfortable environment for class discussion.
Monotonous way of teaching. The class just spends time listening to one another- she has very little input. No practical experience in the field of health communication. Wonderful accent too!
Enjoyed the class with her thoroughly. But hated the group project: caution

Do not take this course with her. Maybe she teaches other courses better, but I have never had such a lazy and disorganized prof. Her expectations are unclear. The content is easy to grasp, so read the textbook! That is why I got an A in the course. Must attend class for participation, but the lectures are unclear repetitions of the book.
AWESOME everyone got an A+
I like how she creates a comfortable atmosphere during class so that we can talk openly in front of our peers.

As I recall, she spent the entire first class trying to get people to drop out. Not exactly an inspiring lecturer. Quizzes were very weird. It's as if the course material was so easy that she decided the only way to trip people up would be to play impossible semantic word games. Then again, that could be said of the entire CMN program. Pointless.
I learnt much more than I ever thought I would from this class; thanks to Dr. Ahmed for giving this opportunity!

Don?t listen to angry/negative people that did poorly in the class. Rukhsana is a great teacher! Come on?you know better?I like her approach to teaching; what a great idea to have poster presentations! I highly recommend taking this class with her.
Terrible director.  No ability to articulate her ideas or lead a group of people to a common educational goal.

I absolutely loved my class with Professor Ahmed! Shes sometimes a little ambiguous, but shes always there to help you and offers extra credit assignments if you needt them and want them...I love her, take a class with her!
I recommend her. Although, at first, could appear tough...turned out to be very understanding:) I felt she had too many assignments though.
Kind, knowledgeable & fair! Does not like when you talk during lecture...
Excellent Professor. Cares about the students. Do take her class!

Found her boring. Way too tentative in her teaching methods. Nothing innovative in her lectures, straight from the textbook. Treats the class like elementary school children rather than university students. Does not clarify information well.
